description:
&lt;p&gt;Ward F22 is a 21 bedded gastrointestinal unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a part time receptionist to join our friendly team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The hours will be 20 hours per week. Monday - Thursday 3pm-7pm and 4 hours on Friday&#39;s (start/finish times are flexible).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be responsible for providing a friendly and efficient service to patients, visitors and professional bodies. Applicants must be confident communicators with the ability to liaise with staff at all levels.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Essential qualities include strong organisational and time management skills with the ability to multi-task and work under pressure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants should have demonstrable experience of working in a patient orientated environment. Applicants should be experienced in using I.T. systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full training will be given to the right candidate on all hospital based systems along with a structured induction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mandy Mulligan&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;amanda.mulligan@nuh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 0115 9249924 ext 69022&lt;/p&gt;
